50|$|Iranian <b>Islamic</b> <b>Republic</b> Day (روز جمهوری اسلامی) is Farvardin 12 that {{known as}} Ruz e Jomhuri ye Eslāmi. This {{day is a}} {{national}} and a public holiday in Iran. On Iranian Solar Hijri calendar, this day is registered as {{the anniversary of the}} 1979 establishment of the <b>Islamic</b> <b>Republic</b> and celebrated by people. Two months after victory of the Islamic Revolution on 1979, the new government held Iranian <b>Islamic</b> <b>Republic</b> referendum on the 10th and 11th of Farvadin (30th and 31 March) for changing the Pahlavi dynasty with an <b>Islamic</b> <b>Republic.</b> On 12 Farvadin, the referendum results was announced that 98.2 percent of the Iranian people voted to <b>Islamic</b> <b>Republic.</b>|$|R
